data.title: UK's Princess Beatrice marries fiance in private ceremony | NCAA Philippines
data.meta_description: The two tied the knot in a secret ceremony at Windsor Castle attended by the Queen, Prince Philip, and other close family members.
data.text:
Queen Elizabeth's granddaughter Princess Beatrice has married her fiance Edoardo Mapelli Mozzi.

According a report from CNN, the two tied the knot in a private ceremony at Windsor Castle attended by the Queen, Prince Philip, and other close family members.

The royal couple announced their engagement in September, but they reportedly canceled their wedding due to the lockdown in the United Kingdom amid the coronavirus pandemic.

Princess Beatrice is the eldest daughter of Prince Andrew and Sarah, Duchess of York. She is ninth in the line of succession to the British throne.
